==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Demobilization
<hw>De*mob`i*li*za"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>d⟦eacute⟧mobilisation</ets>. See <er>Mobilization</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Mil.)</fld> <def>The disorganization or disarming of troops which
have previously been mobilized or called into active service; the change
from a war footing to a peace footing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Demobilize</ent>⟦br⟧
